The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Kalyani Brakes to be renamed

 New Delhi, July 16 (PTI): German auto component major Bosch today bought over the stake of the Kalyani group in brake manufacturer Kalyani Brakes and decided to rename the company Bosch Chassis Systems India. Bosch plans to use the unit as a global manufacturing base for modern braking systems.

 The company today signed an agreement to double its holding in Kalyani Brakes to 80 per cent.

 The transaction is on the basis of transfer of shares between promoters, subject to Indian regulations. Kalyani Brakes was previously operated as a joint venture between Bosch and the Kalyani group, each with a 40 per cent holding, the company said. 




